  "title": "",
  "movie": "에이브의 쿠킹 다이어리 (Abe)",
  "duration_sec": 758.43,
  "audio_url": "https://pub-7f9ded590f88439d8f48752f6639e723.r2.dev/2020-09-15_screen_english.mp3",
  "artwork_generated_url": "",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 12.7,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.7,
      "end": 35.05,
      "text": "영화와 영어 공부를 동시에 일석이조 스크린 잉글리쉬 타임"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.05,
      "end": 40.67,
      "text": "9월에 함께하고 있는 영화는 요리가 섞이면 마음까지 섞일 수 있을까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 41.11,
      "end": 43.07,
      "text": "그런 질문을 던져주는 영화죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.25,
      "end": 45.01,
      "text": "에이브, 에이브의 쿠킹 다이어리"
    },
    {
      "start": 45.01,
      "end": 46.93,
      "text": "아, 하이 크리스"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.93,
      "end": 47.87,
      "text": "Hello, good morning everyone."
    },
    {
      "start": 48.09,
      "end": 48.69,
      "text": "How's it going?"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.13,
      "end": 49.71,
      "text": "Yeah, fine."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.83,
      "end": 50.51,
      "text": "How about you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.79,
      "end": 51.75,
      "text": "I'm doing, you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 51.91,
      "end": 52.15,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 52.27,
      "end": 52.81,
      "text": "Same, same."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.85,
      "end": 55.63,
      "text": "What do you think about that expression?"
    },
    {
      "start": 56.49,
      "end": 60.69,
      "text": "요리가 섞이면 마음까지 섞일 수 있다라는 말을 들으셨는데"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.69,
      "end": 62.19,
      "text": "과연 어떻게 생각하세요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.41,
      "end": 63.17,
      "text": "이해하십니까?"
    },
    {
      "start": 63.17,
      "end": 65.23,
      "text": "Kumara, in fusion. You're talking about fusion."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.35,
      "end": 65.67,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 65.73,
      "end": 66.39,
      "text": "Fusion cooking."
    },
    {
      "start": 67.11,
      "end": 73.35,
      "text": "Well, if you use different or new ingredients, you do think of new things because,"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.51,
      "end": 77.07,
      "text": "Oh, what's this? I've never seen this before. Where is this from?"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.27,
      "end": 82.87,
      "text": "If you do some research, you can learn about a new cuisine and maybe even a new culture"
    },
    {
      "start": 82.87,
      "end": 84.91,
      "text": "if you do your research."
    },
    {
      "start": 84.91,
      "end": 91.49,
      "text": "맞아요. 문화도 섞이고 또 집중하다 보면 마음도 충분히 섞일 수 있는 일이 아닐까 싶습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.49,
      "end": 97.09,
      "text": "And then when you meet someone from that region or that country, you have something to talk about."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.21,
      "end": 97.47,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.47,
      "end": 100.09,
      "text": "I think that's the best part about trying lots of food."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.59,
      "end": 106.51,
      "text": "Because if you don't, like if I come to Korea and I don't know any Korean food, it can be hard to talk to people."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.63,
      "end": 106.77,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.77,
      "end": 108.89,
      "text": "I just know pizza and hamburgers."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.55,
      "end": 112.93,
      "text": "꼬막 비빔밥이라도. 꼬막 비빔밥. My favorite."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.33,
      "end": 116.13,
      "text": "And, 아, 그거 아니까. 공통 주제 있잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.59,
      "end": 120.29,
      "text": "그래요. 이와 같이 음식이 얼마나 중요한 역할을 하는지 모릅니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.65,
      "end": 123.63,
      "text": "아, 오늘 꼬막 비빔밥 한번 비벼 먹어야 되겠네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.87,
      "end": 124.67,
      "text": "It's so good."
    },
    {
      "start": 125.07,
      "end": 125.33,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 125.45,
      "end": 126.21,
      "text": "Something about it."
    },
    {
      "start": 126.21,
      "end": 126.61,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 126.99,
      "end": 129.23,
      "text": "And here's one more interesting thing in this movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.65,
      "end": 133.21,
      "text": "There were many scenes of using social networks here and there."
    },
    {
      "start": 133.29,
      "end": 134.33,
      "text": "Lots of social media."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.53,
      "end": 134.89,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.07,
      "end": 135.97,
      "text": "So I can say it like this."
    },
    {
      "start": 136.17,
      "end": 137.79,
      "text": "I felt like it's a young movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 138.39,
      "end": 138.89,
      "text": "Oh, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 138.89,
      "end": 142.57,
      "text": "약간 젊은 느낌의 그런 영화인 것 같다는 생각을 했어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.75,
      "end": 144.65,
      "text": "Abe is from the young generation."
    },
    {
      "start": 144.79,
      "end": 145.03,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 145.29,
      "end": 147.17,
      "text": "The social media generation."
    },
    {
      "start": 147.41,
      "end": 155.53,
      "text": "So he's using all these different social media platforms to find recipes, to share his cooking creations."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.95,
      "end": 157.41,
      "text": "To have a chat with friends."
    },
    {
      "start": 157.53,
      "end": 159.69,
      "text": "He doesn't meet friends face to face."
    },
    {
      "start": 159.81,
      "end": 160.83,
      "text": "It's kind of sad."
    },
    {
      "start": 160.99,
      "end": 161.31,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 161.31,
      "end": 162.49,
      "text": "He meets them online."
    },
    {
      "start": 162.59,
      "end": 162.91,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 163.07,
      "end": 164.99,
      "text": "But now he has a new friend, Chico."
    },
    {
      "start": 164.99,
      "end": 165.59,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 165.59,
      "end": 169.09,
      "text": "나이 차이는 좀 있지만 그래도 친구가 될 수 있겠죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 169.13,
      "end": 169.87,
      "text": "한참 형님이죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 170.89,
      "end": 171.09,
      "text": "Chico."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.41,
      "end": 176.69,
      "text": "어쨌든 이렇게 소셜 네트워크가 굉장히 자주 사용이 됐는데 이게 왜 그러냐면"
    },
    {
      "start": 176.69,
      "end": 178.39,
      "text": "이 감독 있잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 178.73,
      "end": 181.31,
      "text": "페난도 그로스테인 안드레이리 감독이요."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.61,
      "end": 184.31,
      "text": "소셜 네트워크를 아주 자주 활용을 하는 사람이래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 184.53,
      "end": 185.01,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 185.21,
      "end": 189.29,
      "text": "He actually got into media from a very young age."
    },
    {
      "start": 189.45,
      "end": 190.63,
      "text": "He was a teenager."
    },
    {
      "start": 190.63,
      "end": 194.23,
      "text": "He started writing articles for internet sites."
    },
    {
      "start": 194.23,
      "end": 200.39,
      "text": "And he still uses social media to promote all his documentaries, his movies."
    },
    {
      "start": 200.75,
      "end": 204.11,
      "text": "So it's a big part of his career and his life."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.33,
      "end": 207.53,
      "text": "Oh, it can be a very useful way to promote the movies, right?"
    },
    {
      "start": 207.67,
      "end": 208.03,
      "text": "Definitely."
    },
    {
      "start": 208.23,
      "end": 208.53,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 208.57,
      "end": 209.63,
      "text": "Especially for young people."
    },
    {
      "start": 209.77,
      "end": 212.53,
      "text": "Nowadays, they're not watching so much TV."
    },
    {
      "start": 212.71,
      "end": 214.29,
      "text": "They're on their social media."
    },
    {
      "start": 214.33,
      "end": 214.87,
      "text": "That's right."
    },
    {
      "start": 214.89,
      "end": 215.69,
      "text": "A lot more."
    },
    {
      "start": 215.69,
      "end": 216.69,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.23,
      "end": 219.41,
      "text": "어쨌든 제가 알아보니까요."
    },
    {
      "start": 219.41,
      "end": 224.07,
      "text": "He has more than 15 million followers in his social network."
    },
    {
      "start": 224.37,
      "end": 225.67,
      "text": "Oh, which one is that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 225.83,
      "end": 226.85,
      "text": "와, 그러게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.99,
      "end": 228.67,
      "text": "그거는 뭐 노코멘트겠고."
    },
    {
      "start": 228.71,
      "end": 229.51,
      "text": "사진 올리는 거?"
    },
    {
      "start": 230.01,
      "end": 230.63,
      "text": "큰 수는 거?"
    },
    {
      "start": 230.83,
      "end": 231.21,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 231.35,
      "end": 232.45,
      "text": "자세히는 모르겠고."
    },
    {
      "start": 232.53,
      "end": 232.85,
      "text": "Anyway."
    },
    {
      "start": 233.13,
      "end": 233.27,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 233.39,
      "end": 236.31,
      "text": "팔로워 수가 한 1,500만 명 이상이 된다고 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.57,
      "end": 237.87,
      "text": "He's an influencer."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.07,
      "end": 238.35,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.73,
      "end": 240.57,
      "text": "굉장히 influence하죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.07,
      "end": 242.55,
      "text": "오늘 장면 먼저 듣고 오겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 242.55,
      "end": 244.73,
      "text": "Why did you leave Israel?"
    },
    {
      "start": 245.27,
      "end": 250.97,
      "text": "Oh, your grand mom did not want her daughter to fight in the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.15,
      "end": 252.87,
      "text": "I already did that for her."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.27,
      "end": 255.67,
      "text": "So then why did you fight in the first place?"
    },
    {
      "start": 256.33,
      "end": 265.89,
      "text": "Yeah, I always wanted to do my part to make sure that after thousands of years of persecution that would never happen again."
    },
    {
      "start": 265.89,
      "end": 273.39,
      "text": "네, 지금 이번에는 에이브가요, 외가죠, 유대교 성인식 행사에 참석을 한 장면인데,"
    },
    {
      "start": 273.99,
      "end": 278.77,
      "text": "then he asked his grandpa some questions that I was also curious about."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.05,
      "end": 280.21,
      "text": "At the bar mitzvah."
    },
    {
      "start": 280.27,
      "end": 280.55,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 280.83,
      "end": 285.13,
      "text": "At the bar mitzvah, the coming of age ceremony for Jewish people."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.77,
      "end": 291.03,
      "text": "And yeah, he's curious a lot about his Jewish culture and Jewish history."
    },
    {
      "start": 291.19,
      "end": 294.11,
      "text": "So his grandpa is trying to answer his questions."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.11,
      "end": 299.21,
      "text": "Yeah, 그리고 저는 영화 초반부터, I wonder why they came to America."
    },
    {
      "start": 299.97,
      "end": 301.45,
      "text": "왜 미국에 왔을까?"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.85,
      "end": 304.01,
      "text": "이런 궁금증이 좀 있었는데."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.07,
      "end": 304.69,
      "text": "좀 풀렸네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.81,
      "end": 307.85,
      "text": "네, 오늘 대화를 통해서 잘 들을 수가 있었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.13,
      "end": 312.31,
      "text": "이스라엘에도 되게 복잡한 역사가 많이 있잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 312.49,
      "end": 313.61,
      "text": "Very tragic history."
    },
    {
      "start": 314.07,
      "end": 315.35,
      "text": "They were on the run."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.59,
      "end": 318.25,
      "text": "They suffered the holocaust."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.31,
      "end": 318.59,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.07,
      "end": 320.55,
      "text": "Unimaginable tragedy."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.55,
      "end": 324.71,
      "text": "And the grandpa was witness to part of that."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.85,
      "end": 325.03,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.03,
      "end": 326.87,
      "text": "And he knows that history very well."
    },
    {
      "start": 327.05,
      "end": 329.55,
      "text": "So he's trying to explain that to Abe."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.55,
      "end": 354.61,
      "text": "So there are some similarities with our country."
    },
    {
      "start": 354.61,
      "end": 360.43,
      "text": "They've been constantly on the run, historically, trying to find their homeland."
    },
    {
      "start": 361.23,
      "end": 367.61,
      "text": "And Israel, their current homeland, is claimed as a holy place by many different groups."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.81,
      "end": 373.03,
      "text": "So they're still experiencing conflict and war."
    },
    {
      "start": 373.27,
      "end": 373.57,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 374.07,
      "end": 376.65,
      "text": "일단 어떤 단어들이 있었는지 알아볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 376.65,
      "end": 383.82,
      "text": "In the first place, 이게 무슨 의미냐면, 장소적인 의미가 아니에요."
    },
    {
      "start": 384.12,
      "end": 384.38,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 384.9,
      "end": 389.26,
      "text": "In the first place, 보통 마지막에 붙이죠, 문제나."
    },
    {
      "start": 389.88,
      "end": 395.14,
      "text": "애당초, 우선이라는 의미로 in the first place라는 표현이 쓰입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 395.92,
      "end": 396.8,
      "text": "Do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 397.14,
      "end": 398.2,
      "text": "Do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 398.3,
      "end": 398.92,
      "text": "무슨 의미일까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.92,
      "end": 399.54,
      "text": "Do your part."
    },
    {
      "start": 399.8,
      "end": 400.68,
      "text": "Come on."
    },
    {
      "start": 400.88,
      "end": 401.96,
      "text": "I'm doing my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 402.18,
      "end": 404.02,
      "text": "You need to do your part."
    },
    {
      "start": 404.02,
      "end": 405.24,
      "text": "딱 와닿죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 405.5,
      "end": 407.04,
      "text": "이렇게 적절한 예문과 함께."
    },
    {
      "start": 407.9,
      "end": 409.08,
      "text": "내 몫을 하다."
    },
    {
      "start": 409.22,
      "end": 409.98,
      "text": "라는 의미입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 410.12,
      "end": 410.92,
      "text": "Do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 411.4,
      "end": 412.12,
      "text": "Persecution."
    },
    {
      "start": 412.44,
      "end": 413.16,
      "text": "Persecution."
    },
    {
      "start": 413.34,
      "end": 414.8,
      "text": "이 단어의 철자를 알려드리면,"
    },
    {
      "start": 414.94,
      "end": 418.64,
      "text": "P-E-R-S-E-Q-U-T-I-O-N이라고 해서,"
    },
    {
      "start": 419.02,
      "end": 420.88,
      "text": "박해라는 의미가 되겠어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 421.12,
      "end": 423.78,
      "text": "The Jewish people suffered a lot of persecution."
    },
    {
      "start": 423.94,
      "end": 425.26,
      "text": "Yeah, kind of oppression."
    },
    {
      "start": 425.52,
      "end": 425.74,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 425.74,
      "end": 426.24,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 426.24,
      "end": 428.42,
      "text": "그러면 이 내용 한 번 더 들어보겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 429.58,
      "end": 430.78,
      "text": "Why did you leave Israel?"
    },
    {
      "start": 431.32,
      "end": 433.5,
      "text": "Oh, your grandmom."
    },
    {
      "start": 434.18,
      "end": 437.04,
      "text": "I did not want her daughter to fight in the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 437.2,
      "end": 438.9,
      "text": "I already did that for her."
    },
    {
      "start": 439.24,
      "end": 441.74,
      "text": "So then why did you fight in the first place?"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.36,
      "end": 449.66,
      "text": "Yeah, I always wanted to do my part to make sure that after thousands of years of persecution,"
    },
    {
      "start": 450.2,
      "end": 451.96,
      "text": "that would never happen again."
    },
    {
      "start": 452.65,
      "end": 459.65,
      "text": "Yeah, as I said already, that's a precious conversation between Abe and his grandfather here."
    },
    {
      "start": 459.65,
      "end": 460.35,
      "text": "Very precious."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.85,
      "end": 465.03,
      "text": "Nowadays, many kids do not have these kinds of conversations."
    },
    {
      "start": 465.41,
      "end": 466.43,
      "text": "It's sad."
    },
    {
      "start": 466.97,
      "end": 467.61,
      "text": "Sad합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 467.79,
      "end": 470.51,
      "text": "Ask your grandparents about their past."
    },
    {
      "start": 470.73,
      "end": 472.27,
      "text": "They like it."
    },
    {
      "start": 472.41,
      "end": 473.75,
      "text": "They want to talk about it."
    },
    {
      "start": 473.75,
      "end": 478.45,
      "text": "Oh, 역사에 대해서도 한 번 할아버지와 이야기해보는 것도 되게 좋을 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 478.71,
      "end": 479.35,
      "text": "Yeah, 아빠라도."
    },
    {
      "start": 479.63,
      "end": 480.01,
      "text": "Oh, 맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 480.01,
      "end": 481.73,
      "text": "우리 아빠한테 주문해줘요."
    },
    {
      "start": 481.85,
      "end": 482.39,
      "text": "아, 맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 483.29,
      "end": 484.37,
      "text": "자, 내용 한 번 알아보죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 484.81,
      "end": 486.49,
      "text": "Why did you leave Israel?"
    },
    {
      "start": 486.73,
      "end": 489.69,
      "text": "이게 바로 제가 질문하고 싶었던 내용입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 489.71,
      "end": 490.27,
      "text": "Good question."
    },
    {
      "start": 490.87,
      "end": 492.17,
      "text": "Why did you leave Israel, Grandpa?"
    },
    {
      "start": 492.43,
      "end": 494.27,
      "text": "Why did you leave Israel?"
    },
    {
      "start": 494.51,
      "end": 495.03,
      "text": "이해 되시죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 495.43,
      "end": 498.33,
      "text": "왜 이스라엘을 떠나셨어요? 라는 거예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 498.33,
      "end": 506.69,
      "text": "Because he's very strict in his religious practices, and Israel is the home of the Jewish people, so why did you leave?"
    },
    {
      "start": 506.77,
      "end": 507.19,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 508.15,
      "end": 512.33,
      "text": "Your grandmom did not want our daughter to fight in the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.33,
      "end": 519.85,
      "text": "네, 할아버지의 발음을 들으셨는데 원어민의 발음은 아니었지만 그래도 잘 들리는 편이었어요, 그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 519.87,
      "end": 520.91,
      "text": "Yeah, I could understand."
    },
    {
      "start": 521.07,
      "end": 521.23,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 521.23,
      "end": 527.51,
      "text": "Your grandmom, 너의 할머니가, did not want, 원하지 않았어."
    },
    {
      "start": 527.91,
      "end": 530.97,
      "text": "Our daughter to fight in the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 531.17,
      "end": 535.23,
      "text": "라고 했으니까 우리 딸이 군에 가서 싸우는 걸 원치 않았어."
    },
    {
      "start": 535.37,
      "end": 535.79,
      "text": "라는 겁니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 536.03,
      "end": 537.79,
      "text": "여기서의 우리 딸은 누굴까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 538.27,
      "end": 539.81,
      "text": "A, B의 mother이 되겠죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 540.15,
      "end": 540.65,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 540.75,
      "end": 541.05,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 541.39,
      "end": 544.71,
      "text": "And the Israeli army is very, very unique."
    },
    {
      "start": 544.71,
      "end": 552.53,
      "text": "Because usually, men, only men, are forced or mandated to serve in the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 552.75,
      "end": 555.93,
      "text": "Just like Korea, only men have to go to the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 556.19,
      "end": 558.29,
      "text": "But Israel is a little different."
    },
    {
      "start": 558.89,
      "end": 564.39,
      "text": "Women are also, they're mandated to serve in the Israeli military."
    },
    {
      "start": 564.87,
      "end": 569.45,
      "text": "So that's why the daughter, Abe's mom, had to go to the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 569.73,
      "end": 571.51,
      "text": "So if she didn't leave."
    },
    {
      "start": 571.51,
      "end": 576.33,
      "text": "Anyway, there are enemies in all sides out of Israel."
    },
    {
      "start": 576.67,
      "end": 577.25,
      "text": "They're surrounded."
    },
    {
      "start": 578.19,
      "end": 578.53,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 579.43,
      "end": 581.09,
      "text": "다음 문장 또 알아볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 582.39,
      "end": 584.27,
      "text": "I already did that for her."
    },
    {
      "start": 584.41,
      "end": 584.73,
      "text": "Aha!"
    },
    {
      "start": 584.97,
      "end": 585.69,
      "text": "할아버지께서."
    },
    {
      "start": 585.95,
      "end": 587.99,
      "text": "I already did that for her."
    },
    {
      "start": 588.11,
      "end": 589.31,
      "text": "이렇게 이야기를 했습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 589.51,
      "end": 591.23,
      "text": "Oh, he fought for his daughter."
    },
    {
      "start": 591.39,
      "end": 591.61,
      "text": "Oh!"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.17,
      "end": 595.81,
      "text": "내가 이미 그 일을 했지라는 이야기입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 596.39,
      "end": 597.59,
      "text": "Yeah, he went to the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 597.59,
      "end": 598.13,
      "text": "Uh-huh."
    },
    {
      "start": 598.85,
      "end": 601.59,
      "text": "So then why did you fight in the first place?"
    },
    {
      "start": 601.59,
      "end": 602.11,
      "text": "아하!"
    },
    {
      "start": 602.23,
      "end": 604.81,
      "text": "배웠던 고문이 끝부분에 딱 들렸죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 605.37,
      "end": 610.31,
      "text": "그러면 왜 처음부터 할아버지는 싸우신 거예요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 610.81,
      "end": 613.53,
      "text": "그러면 처음부터 할아버지는 왜 싸우셨는데요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 613.73,
      "end": 614.51,
      "text": "라고 질문을 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 614.65,
      "end": 615.51,
      "text": "What's the reason?"
    },
    {
      "start": 615.67,
      "end": 617.53,
      "text": "Oh, his grandson is very logical."
    },
    {
      "start": 617.95,
      "end": 618.35,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 618.49,
      "end": 619.37,
      "text": "Oh, 똑똑해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 619.61,
      "end": 620.43,
      "text": "Very smart."
    },
    {
      "start": 620.53,
      "end": 620.73,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 620.83,
      "end": 621.71,
      "text": "Wants to know everything."
    },
    {
      "start": 622.47,
      "end": 625.11,
      "text": "I always wanted to do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 625.11,
      "end": 626.73,
      "text": "이것도 딱 들리시죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 627.27,
      "end": 628.43,
      "text": "Do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 628.43,
      "end": 631.23,
      "text": "나는 내 몫을 하고 싶었던 것이야."
    },
    {
      "start": 631.39,
      "end": 633.19,
      "text": "I always wanted to do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 633.63,
      "end": 635.97,
      "text": "나는 늘 내 몫을 하고 싶었거든."
    },
    {
      "start": 636.17,
      "end": 640.71,
      "text": "Ah, that's a perfect reason for joining the army and fighting for your country."
    },
    {
      "start": 640.85,
      "end": 641.11,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 641.25,
      "end": 642.97,
      "text": "It was his choice for his country."
    },
    {
      "start": 643.47,
      "end": 646.87,
      "text": "He had a good attitude about army and about army service."
    },
    {
      "start": 647.13,
      "end": 647.29,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 647.29,
      "end": 649.81,
      "text": "I always wanted to do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 650.61,
      "end": 657.11,
      "text": "To make sure that after thousands of years of persecution, that would never happen again."
    },
    {
      "start": 657.37,
      "end": 658.79,
      "text": "아, 감동입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 659.05,
      "end": 659.17,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 659.59,
      "end": 665.11,
      "text": "To make sure that after thousands of years of persecution, 이라고 했으니까,"
    },
    {
      "start": 665.87,
      "end": 669.61,
      "text": "수천 년의, thousands of years of persecution, 딱 들리셨죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 669.69,
      "end": 670.39,
      "text": "Persecution."
    },
    {
      "start": 670.39,
      "end": 675.81,
      "text": "네, 수천 년의 박해가 끝난 후에, that would never happen again."
    },
    {
      "start": 676.17,
      "end": 680.71,
      "text": "다시는 그 일이 일어나지 않도록, to make sure, 하기 위해서라는 이야기입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 681.03,
      "end": 683.79,
      "text": "It's a relative young nation, Israel."
    },
    {
      "start": 684.01,
      "end": 684.11,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 684.25,
      "end": 691.81,
      "text": "1948, after World War II, it was founded right after all those years of persecution."
    },
    {
      "start": 692.37,
      "end": 696.33,
      "text": "So, yeah, he did his part to protect Israel."
    },
    {
      "start": 696.55,
      "end": 699.09,
      "text": "Yeah, it was heartbreaking history, wasn't it?"
    },
    {
      "start": 699.09,
      "end": 700.03,
      "text": "Very heartbreaking."
    },
    {
      "start": 700.03,
      "end": 702.51,
      "text": "Yeah, 이 내용 한 번 더 들어보겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 702.51,
      "end": 704.91,
      "text": "Why did you leave Israel?"
    },
    {
      "start": 705.45,
      "end": 711.15,
      "text": "Oh, your grand mom did not want the daughter to fight in the army."
    },
    {
      "start": 711.31,
      "end": 713.07,
      "text": "I already did that for her."
    },
    {
      "start": 713.45,
      "end": 715.85,
      "text": "So then why did you fight in the first place?"
    },
    {
      "start": 716.51,
      "end": 719.09,
      "text": "Yeah, I always wanted to do my part."
    },
    {
      "start": 719.53,
      "end": 726.07,
      "text": "To make sure that after thousands of years of persecution, that would never happen again."
    },
    {
      "start": 726.07,
      "end": 733.47,
      "text": "네, 오늘은 이스라엘의 역사에 대해서도 우리가 좀 풍부하게 이야기를 할 수가 있었던 기회였어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 733.61,
      "end": 735.77,
      "text": "I'm going to have to go home and study more."
    },
    {
      "start": 736.01,
      "end": 738.07,
      "text": "We learned about this in school a lot."
    },
    {
      "start": 738.53,
      "end": 739.95,
      "text": "멋지다, 그리스 씨."
    },
    {
      "start": 740.05,
      "end": 746.73,
      "text": "American students learn about Israeli history, but I forgot a lot, so I got to brush up on my history."
    },
    {
      "start": 746.73,
      "end": 747.79,
      "text": "그게 매력입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 747.99,
      "end": 750.73,
      "text": "인간은 자고로 잊어버려야 그게 매력인 거예요."
    },
    {
      "start": 750.99,
      "end": 753.07,
      "text": "그래야지 다시 노력해서 또 채우고 그러죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 753.23,
      "end": 753.43,
      "text": "그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 754.11,
      "end": 755.05,
      "text": "That's a good attitude."
    },
    {
      "start": 755.27,
      "end": 756.35,
      "text": "네, 기대할게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 756.59,
      "end": 758.43,
      "text": "오늘 스크린 잉글리쉬는 여기까지고요."
    }
  ]
}